The paper deals with the analysis of parametrised and reconfigurable systems, which are typically modelled using Markov chains. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), which includes papers on formal methods and verification. The paper also involves the use of algorithms and data structures, which suggests the category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques, which could place it in the category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with systems that can be reconfigured, which suggests the category cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves the use of model transformations, which could place it in the category cs.PL (Programming Languages).
